  "prompt": "Which stands for the chemical disphosphorus pentasulphide: P4S10 or P2S5?",
  "response": "Disphosphorus pentasulfide is represented by the chemical formula \\( P_2S_5 \\). The prefix \"di-\" indicates two phosphorus (P) atoms, and \"penta-\" indicates five sulfur (S) atoms. Therefore, \\( P_2S_5 \\) is the correct formula for disphosphorus pentasulfide. \\( P_4S_{10} \\) would represent a molecule containing four phosphorus atoms and ten sulfur atoms, which is not what disphosphorus pentasulfide refers to.",
